Weeping cherry blossoms (shidare-zakura) bathed in morning sunlight, on Arashiyama's Nakanoshima island.
</p>
<p class="jp">
嵐山・中之島のしだれ桜が朝日に照らされる。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Sakura" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Weeping cherry blossoms (shidare-zakura) bathed in morning sunlight, on Arashiyama's Nakanoshima island. 嵐山・中之島のしだれ桜が朝日に照らされる。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2603_A7R00584_edit.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2603_A7R00584_edit.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Blue Osaka・ブルー大阪</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260329/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Blue Osaka・ブルー大阪" /><published>2026-03-29T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-03-29T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/osaka</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260329/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Looking east at dusk along Osaka's Okawa river, from above Nakanoshima island. Among the bridges in this photo are the Tenjinbashi and Tenmabashi. The cherry blossoms along the river haven't really started to come out yet.
</p>
<p class="jp">
大阪の大川沿いの夕暮れ時、中之島の上から東を眺める。
この写真には天神橋と天満橋が含まれている。川沿いの桜はまだ咲き始めていない。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Osaka" /><category term="Views" /><category term="Dusk" /><category term="Rivers" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Looking east at dusk along Osaka's Okawa river, from above Nakanoshima island. Among the bridges in this photo are the Tenjinbashi and Tenmabashi. The cherry blossoms along the river haven't really started to come out yet. 大阪の大川沿いの夕暮れ時、中之島の上から東を眺める。 この写真には天神橋と天満橋が含まれている。川沿いの桜はまだ咲き始めていない。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2603_A7R00481_edit-2.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2603_A7R00481_edit-2.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Honmanji・本満寺</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260328/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Honmanji・本満寺" /><published>2026-03-28T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-03-28T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/honmanji</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260328/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Looking up from under the giant weeping cherry tree at Honmanji Temple.
</p>
<p class="jp">
本満寺の巨大な枝垂れ桜の下から見上げる。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Sakura" /><category term="Temples" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Looking up from under the giant weeping cherry tree at Honmanji Temple. 本満寺の巨大な枝垂れ桜の下から見上げる。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2603_A7R00439_edit.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2603_A7R00439_edit.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Nakanoshima・中之島</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260327/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Nakanoshima・中之島" /><published>2026-03-27T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-03-27T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/nakanoshima</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260327/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Cherry tree in front of the Togetsukyo bridge is illuminated by the sun before it goes behind the mountains. None are full yet, but almost every cherry tree in Arashiyama is blooming now.
</p>
<p class="jp">
渡月橋の前の桜の木が、山の向こうに行く前の太陽に照らされている。まだ満開の桜はないが、嵐山の桜はほとんどすべて開花している。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Sakura" /><category term="Togetsu Bridge" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Cherry tree in front of the Togetsukyo bridge is illuminated by the sun before it goes behind the mountains. None are full yet, but almost every cherry tree in Arashiyama is blooming now. 渡月橋の前の桜の木が、山の向こうに行く前の太陽に照らされている。まだ満開の桜はないが、嵐山の桜はほとんどすべて開花している。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2603_DSCF1796_edit.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2603_DSCF1796_edit.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Bamboo Path・竹林</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260326/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Bamboo Path・竹林" /><published>2026-03-26T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-03-26T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/chikurin</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260326/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Walking through the bamboo path, I find a moment all my own.
</p>
<p class="jp">
竹林を歩きながら、自分だけのひとときを見つける。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Bamboo Grove" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Walking through the bamboo path, I find a moment all my own. 竹林を歩きながら、自分だけのひとときを見つける。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2603_IMG_3494.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2603_IMG_3494.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Maruyama Park・円山公園</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260325/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Maruyama Park・円山公園" /><published>2026-03-25T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-03-25T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/maruyama</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260325/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
More and more cherry blossoms popping up around town. These weeping sakura are at Maruyama Park.
</p>
<p class="jp">
街中で桜の花が次々と咲き始めている。このしだれ桜は丸山公園にある。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Higashiyama" /><category term="Parks" /><category term="Sakura" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[More and more cherry blossoms popping up around town. These weeping sakura are at Maruyama Park. 街中で桜の花が次々と咲き始めている。このしだれ桜は丸山公園にある。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2603_A7R00392_edit.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2603_A7R00392_edit.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Sakura Morning・桜の朝</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260324/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Sakura Morning・桜の朝" /><published>2026-03-24T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-03-24T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/oigawa</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260324/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Pink and green along the Oigawa river in Arashiyama.
</p>
<p class="jp">
嵐山の大堰川沿いに咲く桜の木。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Katsura River" /><category term="Sakura" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Pink and green along the Oigawa river in Arashiyama. 嵐山の大堰川沿いに咲く桜の木。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2603_A7R00297_edit.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2603_A7R00297_edit.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Early Bloom・早咲き</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260323/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Early Bloom・早咲き" /><published>2026-03-23T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-03-23T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/sakura-togetsu</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260323/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Cherry Blossoms are starting to come out in Arashiyama.
</p>
<p class="jp">
嵐山では桜が咲き始めている。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Togetsu Bridge" /><category term="Sakura" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Cherry Blossoms are starting to come out in Arashiyama. 嵐山では桜が咲き始めている。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2603_A7R00247_edit.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2603_A7R00247_edit.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Colorful Bridge・カラフルな橋</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260322/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Colorful Bridge・カラフルな橋" /><published>2026-03-22T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-03-22T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/togetsukyo</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260322/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Arashiyama's Togetsukyo bridge at night, illuminated in a special, colorful display.
</p>
<p class="jp">
夜、特別なカラーイルミネーションに彩られた嵐山の渡月橋。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Togetsu Bridge" /><category term="Long Exposure" /><category term="Night" /><category term="Lightup" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Arashiyama's Togetsukyo bridge at night, illuminated in a special, colorful display. 夜、特別なカラーイルミネーションに彩られた嵐山の渡月橋。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2603_A7R00244-HDR.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2603_A7R00244-HDR.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Konoe Cherry Tree・近衛桜</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260321/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Konoe Cherry Tree・近衛桜" /><published>2026-03-21T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-03-21T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/konoe-sakura</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260321/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Closeup on one of the hanging branches of this cherry tree, at the former location of the Konoe Residence in Kyoto Gyoen, the former Imperial Palace park. This "Itozakura" weeping sakura is the most famous cherry tree in the park, drawing many visitors on this spring day. 
</p>
<p class="jp">
旧皇居の庭園である京都御苑内、かつての近衛邸跡にある桜の枝のクローズアップだ。この糸桜（イトザクラ）の品種のしだれ桜は、この庭園で最も有名な桜であり、春の陽気の中、今日も多くの訪問者を集めていた。
</p>

